CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 6, 1954, pg. 1 reads: "Belmar Gardens Opens - The first families took up residence at Belmar Gardens, the East End cooperative development, on Monday. They included William Ivory, left, observing Clarence Rogers, manager, as he presents keys to Mr. and Mrs. Melvyn Newell. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: William Ivory, Clarence Rogers, presenting house keys to Mr. and Mrs. Melvyn Newell, and unknown man, standing in front of brick house in Belmar Gardens
